        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "In India, PCOD (Polycystic Ovarian Disease) and PCOS (Polycystic Ovary Syndrome) are often used interchangeably, but they're not identical. PCOS is the medical term — it's a metabolic endocrine disorder, not just an ovarian structural issue. PCOD may refer to the cysts alone without the metabolic dysfunction. Most Indian doctors use PCOD colloquially, but the metabolic picture is what matters for diagnosis and treatment. arq. diagnoses based on metabolic markers (androgens, insulin, LH:FSH), not just ovarian appearance."
