        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No, PCOS cannot be cured — but it can be managed extremely well. Think of it like diabetes or hypertension: lifelong management, but normal function is achievable. With the right treatment (medication, lifestyle, dietary protocol), most women see regular periods, reduced androgen symptoms, improved fertility, and better energy within 3-6 months. Management matters more than a cure. Many women stop medication after symptom control but maintain lifestyle changes. The goal is symptom remission and metabolic stability, not eradication."
